[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = ElectronLiquidRG","category":"page"},{"location":"#ElectronLiquidRG","page":"Home","title":"ElectronLiquidRG","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for ElectronLiquidRG.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [ElectronLiquidRG]","category":"page"},{"location":"#ElectronLiquidRG.KO","page":"Home","title":"ElectronLiquidRG.KO","text":"function KO(para::ParaMC, kamp=para.kF, kamp2=para.kF; N=100, mix=1.0, verbose=1, ct=false)\n\nCalculate Fs with the self-consistent equation\n```math\nf_s = -\\left< (v_q+f_s)/(1-(v_q+f_s)Π_0) \\right>\n```\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ElectronLiquidRG.c_coeff_phe","page":"Home","title":"ElectronLiquidRG.c_coeff_phe","text":"uPi_0u particle-hole exchange diagram. \n\n(up, up, up, up): the internal bubble is spin down, and there is a Fermi loop contributing a minus sign\n(up, up, down, down): the internal bubble is up and down, and there is no closed Fermi loop, so there is no additional sign.\n\nFor a reference of the diagram sign, according to ElectronLiquid.Ver4.MC_PH subroutine, for rs=1, mass=10.0, Yukawa interaction\n\norder                 upup          updown\n\n1 (exchange)        0.152(1)        0.0 \n2 (PHEr)            0.0088(1)    -0.0119(2)\n2 (PPr)             0.002083     0.02198(42)\n\nWARNING 1: Following the convention of the RG application, we need to add an additional minus to the above results. WARNING 2: The main contributions in the PPr diagrams are from the UV, so it should be compared with Λ∞ - uG0G0u where Λ∞ needs to be fitted.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ElectronLiquidRG.c_coeff_pp","page":"Home","title":"ElectronLiquidRG.c_coeff_pp","text":"-uG0G0*u + #Λ∞ ladder diagram subtracting the constant term. The (up, up, up, up) is zero and (up, up, down, down) is non-zero \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#ElectronLiquidRG.vertex3-Tuple{ElectronLiquid.UEG.ParaMC}","page":"Home","title":"ElectronLiquidRG.vertex3","text":"function vertex3(para::ParaMC;\n\ncalculate particle-particle-pair * R. Only spin (up, up; down, down) is non-zero!\n\nIn the large kamp limit, with kamp2 =0, it approaches to -me^2NF*pi/2/kamp\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ElectronLiquidRG.∂R_∂F_exchange-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"ElectronLiquidRG.∂R_∂F_exchange","text":"function ∂Rs_∂Fs_exchange(paras, Λgrid; ct=false)\n\n return N_F ∂<R_{k_1-k_2}>/∂Fs\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#ElectronLiquidRG.∂R_∂Λ_exchange-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"ElectronLiquidRG.∂R_∂Λ_exchange","text":"function ∂Rs_∂Λ_exchange(paras, Λgrid; ct=false)\n\n return N_F ∂<R_{k_1-k_2}>/∂Λ\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
